data.title: Wikipedia:Featured picture candidates/Elizabeth I
data.text:
Reason

I dunno why such a fantastic picture as never been nominated. It's main article is also featured, and this is perhaps the only proper picture we will get of this historical figure.

Articles this image appears in

Elizabeth I of England, Wealthy historical figures 2008

Creator

Hatfield House

Support as nominator Dengero (talk)

Support Looks good to me. Juliancolton (Talk)

Oppose looks like scan and jpeg artifacting in there. de Bivort

Comment Is the left side cut off? the words appear to go off the page. Calliopejen1 (talk)

Yes. This scan shows the first word, "Non," which is right up against the frame (the frame itself has been cropped). Chick Bowen

Comment. Looks like it was scanned out of a book since you can see the halftoning. Kaldari (talk)

Oppose her headdress is cut off and artefacts --Hadseys ChatContribs

Oppose several problems, but the halftoning can't be fixed. Worthy subject, something better should be available. DurovaCharge!

Not promoted MER-C
